TEXT_29=The first symptom is a between 102 and 106 \u00B0F. An adult usually has a lower fever than a child.
TEXT_28=The flu spreads easily. It can affect a large group of people in a very short amount of time. For example, students and workers get sick within 2 or 3 weeks of the flu's arrival in a school or workplace.
TEXT_27=Flu symptoms will often start quickly. You can start to feel sick about 1-7 days after you come in contact with the virus. Most of the time symptoms appear in 2-3 days.
TEXT_26=Symptoms
TEXT_25=stomach flu
TEXT_24=Sometimes, you can get a virus that makes you throw up or have diarrhea. Some people call this the "." This is a misleading name because this virus is not the actual flu. The flu mostly affects your nose, throat, and lungs.
TEXT_23=People often confuse colds and flu. They are different. But, you might have some of the same symptoms. Most people get a cold several times each year. Most people get the flu only once every few years.
TEXT_22=Most people get the flu when they breathe in tiny droplets from coughs or sneezes of someone who has the flu. You can also catch the flu if you touch something with the virus on it, and then touch your mouth, nose, or eyes.
TEXT_21=The flu is caused by an influenza virus.
